    "• %@" : {

    },
    "• Must be at least 48 miles (≈ 77 km) from home to be considered traveling" : {

    },
    "❖ “And remember your Lord much and exalt [Him with praise] in the evening and the morning” (Quran 3:41)." : {

    },
    "❖ “Call upon Me; I will respond to you” (Quran 40:60)." : {

    },
    "❖ “Is He [not best] who responds to the desperate one when he calls upon Him and removes evil and makes you inheritors of the earth? Is there a deity with Allah? Little do you remember” (Quran 27:62)." : {

    },
    "❖ “O you who have believed, remember Allah with much remembrance” (Quran 33:41)." : {

    },
    "❖ “Say, 'What would my Lord care for you if not for your supplication?'” (Quran 25:77)." : {

    },
    "❖ “So ask forgiveness of Him and then repent to Him. Indeed, my Lord is near and responsive” (Quran 11:61)." : {

    },
    "❖ “So remember Me; I will remember you. And be grateful to Me and do not deny Me” (Quran 2:152)." : {

    },
    "❖ “The men who remember Allah often and the women who do so - for them Allah has prepared forgiveness and a great reward” (Quran 33:35)." : {

    },
    "❖ “Those who have believed and whose hearts are assured by the remembrance of Allah. Unquestionably, by the remembrance of Allah hearts are assured” (Quran 13:28)." : {

    },
    "❖ “When My servants ask you, [O Muḥammad], concerning Me - indeed I am near. I respond to the invocation of the supplicant when he calls upon Me. So let them respond to Me [by obedience] and believe in Me that they may be [rightly] guided” (Quran 2:186)." : {

    },
    "❖ Prophet Muhammad ﷺ said: “Dua is worship” (Tirmidhi 2969)." : {

    },
    "❖ Prophet Muhammad ﷺ said: “Keep your tongue moist with the remembrance of Allah” (Tirmidhi 3375)." : {

    },
    "❖ Prophet Muhammad ﷺ said: “No people gather to remember Allah Almighty but that the angels surround them, mercy covers them, tranquility descends upon them, and Allah mentions them to those near Him” (Muslim 2700)." : {

    },
    "❖ Prophet Muhammad ﷺ said: “Shall I not tell you of the best of your deeds, which is the purest to your King, which raises you among your ranks, which is better for you than spending gold and money in charity...? It is the remembrance of Allah Almighty” (Tirmidhi 3377)." : {

    },
    "❖ Prophet Muhammad ﷺ said: “Shall I not tell you something better than a servant? When you go to bed, say: *SubhanAllah* 33 times (Glory be to Allah), *Alhamdulillah* 33 times (Praise be to Allah), and *Allahu Akbar* 34 times (Allah is the Greatest)” (Bukhari 6318)." : {

    },
    "❖ Prophet Muhammad ﷺ said: “The example of the one who celebrates the Praises of his Lord and the one who does not celebrate His Praises is like the living and the dead” (Bukhari 6407)." : {

    },
    "❖ Prophet Muhammad ﷺ said: “There are two phrases which are light on the tongue, heavy in the balance, and beloved to the Most Merciful: *SubhanAllahi wa bihamdihi, SubhanAllahil Adheem* (Glory is to Allah and praise is to Him. Glory is to Allah, the Most Great)” (Bukhari 6406)." : {

    },
    "❖ Prophet Muhammad ﷺ said: “There is no Muslim who calls upon Allah with a supplication in which there is no sin or severing of family ties, except that Allah will give him one of three things: He will hasten it, store it for him in the Hereafter, or avert from him a similar harm.” They said: “Then we will increase (in supplication).” He ﷺ said: “Allah is more” (Tirmidhi 3573)." : {

    },
    "❖ Prophet Muhammad ﷺ said: “There is nothing more noble in the sight of Allah ﷻ than dua” (Tirmidhi 3370)." : {

    },
    "❖ Prophet Muhammad ﷺ said: “Whoever does not ask Allah ﷻ, He becomes angry with him” (Tirmidhi 3373)." : {

    },
    "❖ Prophet Muhammad ﷺ said: “Whoever says: *La ilaha illallah wahdahu la sharika lah, lahul-mulk wa lahul-hamd, wa huwa 'ala kulli shayin qadir* (None has the right to be worshipped but Allah, the Alone Who has no partner. His is the Dominion and His is the Praise, and He is over all things All-Powerful) one hundred times in a day will have the reward of freeing ten slaves, one hundred good deeds will be recorded for him, one hundred sins will be erased, and he will be protected from Satan until evening. No one will surpass him except someone who has done more” (Bukhari 3293)." : {

