    "Home: %@" : {

    },
    "If a word starts with hamzatul waSl, its pronunciation depends on the third letter of the word. For verbs: if the third letter has a damma, pronounce it with a damma (أُ); if it has a kasra or fatha, pronounce it with a kasra (إِ)." : {

    },
    "If an Alif Mad is followed by a letter with a shaddah, the elongation extends to 6 counts." : {
      "comment" : "",
      "extractionState" : "stale",
      "localizations" : {
        "ms" : {
          "stringUnit" : {
            "state" : "translated",
            "value" : "Jika Alif Mad diikuti oleh huruf yang mempunyai syaddah, pemanjangan bunyi menjadi 6 harakat."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "If you are traveling more than 48 mi (77.25 km), then it is permissible to pray Qasr, where you combine Dhuhr and Asr (2 rakahs each) and Maghrib and Isha (3 and 2 rakahs). Allah said in the Quran, “And when you (Muslims) travel in the land, there is no sin on you if you shorten As-Salah (the prayer)” [Quran, An-Nisa, 4:101]. %@" : {

    },
