    "The best days for righteous deeds; fasting and dhikr are highly encouraged." : {
      "comment" : "",
      "extractionState" : "stale",
      "localizations" : {
        "ms" : {
          "stringUnit" : {
            "state" : "translated",
            "value" : "Hari-hari terbaik untuk beramal soleh; puasa dan zikir sangat digalakkan."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "The combination of ل and ا forms a unique shape: لا." : {

    },
    "The day of sacrifice; fasting is not allowed and sacrifice of an animal is offered." : {
      "comment" : "",
      "extractionState" : "stale",
      "localizations" : {
        "ms" : {
          "stringUnit" : {
            "state" : "translated",
            "value" : "Hari korban; berpuasa tidak dibenarkan dan ibadah korban dilaksanakan."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "The default list view is the standard interface found in many of Apple's first party apps, including Notes. This setting applies everywhere in the app except here in Settings." : {
      "extractionState" : "stale",
      "localizations" : {
        "ms" : {
          "stringUnit" : {
            "state" : "translated",
            "value" : "Paparan senarai lalai ialah antara muka standard yang digunakan dalam banyak aplikasi Apple, termasuk Notes. Tetapan ini digunakan di seluruh aplikasi kecuali di halaman Tetapan."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "The first day of the Islamic calendar; no special acts of worship or celebration are prescribed." : {
      "comment" : "",
      "extractionState" : "stale",
      "localizations" : {
        "ms" : {
          "stringUnit" : {
            "state" : "translated",
            "value" : "Hari pertama dalam kalendar Islam; tiada ibadah atau sambutan khusus yang disyariatkan."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "The letter Hamza has multiple forms, depending on its position and the surrounding vowels or diacritics (tashkeel):" : {

    },
    "The month of fasting begins; all Muslims must fast from Fajr (dawn) to Maghrib (sunset)." : {
      "comment" : "",
      "extractionState" : "stale",
      "localizations" : {
        "ms" : {
          "stringUnit" : {
            "state" : "translated",
            "value" : "Bulan puasa bermula; semua Muslim wajib berpuasa dari Subuh hingga Maghrib."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "The most virtuous nights of the year; increase worship as these nights are beloved to Allah and contain Laylatul Qadr." : {
      "comment" : "",
      "extractionState" : "stale",
      "localizations" : {
        "ms" : {
          "stringUnit" : {
            "state" : "translated",
            "value" : "Malam-malam paling utama dalam setahun; perbanyakkan ibadah kerana malam-malam ini dicintai Allah dan mengandungi Lailatulqadar."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "The Prophet ﷺ intended to fast the 9th to differ from the Jews, making it Sunnah to do so before Ashura." : {
      "comment" : "",
      "extractionState" : "stale",
      "localizations" : {
        "ms" : {
          "stringUnit" : {
            "state" : "translated",
            "value" : "Nabi ﷺ berniat untuk berpuasa pada 9 Muharam bagi membezakan umat Islam daripada Yahudi, menjadikannya sunnah sebelum Asyura."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "The term \"hamzatul waSl\" translates to \"connecting hamza\" or \"hamza of connection.\"" : {

    },
    "The wavy line above a vowel letter is called a 'mad'. It elongates the vowel sound, typically lasting 4 counts." : {

    },
    "These letters serve as vowels when they follow specific diacritics, and as consonants when they begin a word or are preceded by a sukoon." : {

    },
